Plant Height Modelling

height_HTP.Rd

Plant Height Modelling

Usage

height_HTP(
  results,
  canopy,
  plant_height = "PH",
  plot_id = NULL,
  add_zero = TRUE,
  method = c("subplex", "pracmanm", "anms"),
  return_method = FALSE,
  parameters = c(t2 = 67, alpha = 1/600, beta = -1/80),
  fn = sse_exp2_exp
)

Arguments

results

Object of class exploreHTP

canopy

Object of class canopy_HTP

plant_height

string

plot_id

Optional Plot ID. NULL by default

add_zero

TRUE or FALSE. Add zero to the time series.TRUE by default.

method

A vector of the methods to be used, each as a character string. See optimx package. c("subplex", "pracmanm", "anms") by default.

return_method

TRUE or FALSE. To return the method selected for the optimization in the table. FALSE by default.

parameters

(Optional) Initial values for the parameters to be optimized over. c(45, 80) by default.

fn

A function to be minimized (or maximized), with first argument the vector of parameters over which minimization is to take place. It should return a scalar result. Default is sse_exp2_exp.

Value

data.frame

Examples

library(exploreHTP)
data(dt_chips)
results <- read_HTP(
  data = dt_chips,
  genotype = "Gen",
  time = "DAP",
  plot = "Plot",
  traits = c("Canopy", "PH"),
  row = "Row",
  range = "Range"
)
names(results)
#> [1] "summ_traits"      "exp_design_resum" "locals_min_max"   "dt_long"         
out <- canopy_HTP(
  results = results,
  canopy = "Canopy",
  plot_id = c(60, 150),
  correct_max = TRUE,
  add_zero = TRUE
)
names(out)
#> [1] "param" "dt"   
plot(out, plot_id = c(60, 150))

ph_1 <- height_HTP(
  results = results,
  canopy = out,
  plant_height = "PH",
  add_zero = TRUE,
  method = c("nlminb", "anms", "mla", "pracmanm", "subplex"),
  return_method = TRUE,
  parameters = c(t2 = 67, alpha = 1 / 600, beta = -1 / 80),
  fn = sse_exp2_exp
)
plot(
  x = ph_1,
  plot_id = c(60, 150),
  fn = quote(fn_exp2_exp(time, t1, t2, alpha, beta))
)

ph_1$param
#> # A tibble: 2 × 10
#>    plot genotype    row range    t2    alpha    beta    t1 method      sse

ph_2 <- height_HTP(
  results = results,
  canopy = out,
  plant_height = "PH",
  add_zero = TRUE,
  method = c("nlminb", "anms", "mla", "pracmanm", "subplex"),
  return_method = TRUE,
  parameters = c(t2 = 67, alpha = 1 / 600, beta = -1 / 80),
  fn = sse_exp2_lin
)
plot(
  x = ph_2,
  plot_id = c(60, 150),
  fn = quote(fn_exp2_lin(time, t1, t2, alpha, beta))
)
